comments: Robinson (NYK) extends his arm into Olynyk (MIA) and dislodges him from his defensive position.
Bulter (MIA) falls to the floor and makes contact with the ball as Payton (NYK) gathers the rebound.

Adebayo (MIA) makes contact with the ball after it hits the backboard during Payton's (NYK) shot attempt near the rim. After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of goaltending is confirmed.
Bullock (NYK) places his arms around Robinson's (MIA) body and wraps him off ball.
Following the hand off, Bullock (NYK) reaches out and makes marginal contact to Adebayo's (MIA) arm.
Adebayo (MIA) and Randle (NYK) mutually engage in marginal arm to arm contact off ball as both players attempts to establish position. The leg to leg contact that occurs is incidental.
Burks (NYK) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Burks (NYK) and Iguodala (MIA) briefly engage in marginal contact prior to disengaging during the rebound.
Adebayo (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the drive.
Randle (NYK) briefly places his hand on Iguodala's (MIA) back as he simultaneously reaches in and makes contact with the ball. The contact to Iguodala's back is marginal.
Olynyk (MIA) makes clean contact with the ball as Robinson (NYK) starts his upward shooting motion.
Randle (NYK) dislodges Butler (MIA) from his position during the loose ball.
Butler (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position during Barrett's (NYK) driving shot attempt.

Randle (NYK) inadvertently makes contact to Iguodala's (MIA) head/face during the rebound.  Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
